HEADWORD: Hydrocyanide
<hw>Hy`dro*cy"a*nide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A compound of hydrocyanic acid with a base; -- distinguished from a
<contr>cyanide</contr>, in which only the cyanogen so
combines.</def></p>

